The paper introduces a new model for exchangeable data that uses neural network parameterizations of the energy function. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The paper also demonstrates state-of-the-art performance on tasks such as point cloud generation, classification, denoising, and image completion, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), or natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
